I"G	<p>If you are using OSX this is wonderful because you can customise your command line by adding emoji icons to the bash prompt.</p>

<p>You can find icons inside your Edit menu: <code class="highlighter-rouge">Edit -&gt; Emoji &amp; Symbols</code>.</p>

<p>How to add custom icons to our bash?</p>

<p>So edit your <code class="highlighter-rouge">.bash_profile</code> with your favorite editor vim or nano for example, and add this line:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>PS1=" "
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Open <strong>Emoji &amp; Symbol</strong> panel and drag and drop your favorite emoji inside quotation marks.</p>

<p><img src="https://gitlab.com/huckbit/blog-images/raw/master/images/terminal-cust.gif" alt="drag and Drop" class="image--center" /></p>

<p>Depending on terminal settings, nothing may be visible after using drag &amp; drop. Close and reopen you terminal and voilÃ :
<img src="https://gitlab.com/huckbit/blog-images/raw/master/images/terminal-hb.png" alt="my terminal" class="image--center" /></p>

<p>You can customise terminal bash with some others options:</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="text-align: left">code</th>
      <th style="text-align: left">description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">\d</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Current date</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">\t</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Current time</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">\h</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Host name</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">#</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Command number</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">\u</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">User name</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">\W</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Current working directory (ie: Desktop/)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">\w</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Current working directory with full path</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>This is my favourite customisation:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>PS1="ðŸŒ€  \u@\h\W$ "
</code></pre></div></div>

